  <li class="li3"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s1">Descriptive Praise: “Great use of a for loop in your program.”;</span></li>
  <li class="li3"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s1">Constructive Praise: “The program you wrote was really interesting but it would be even better if you tried to use a for loop instead of having all those similar looking lines of code. ”</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="terms-text"><span class="s1">“Criticism” can be defined as a: ‘ Negative expression of disapproval’ – e.g.:</span></p>
<ul class="ul1">
  <li class="li1"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s1">Evaluative Criticism: “That was bad”, “You are bad”;</span></li>
  <li class="li1"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s1">Descriptive Criticism: “That was bad because You are using the wrong coding techmique”;</span></li>
  <li class="li1"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s1">Constructive Criticism: “The for loop wasn’t as good as it could be – I wonder if You could use a while loop?”</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="terms-text"><span class="s1">Please try to use Praise when commenting on Submissions from other Users. If You are going to use Criticism, please try to ensure it is Constructive Criticism; avoid Descriptive or Evaluative Criticism.</span></p>
